Being curvy isn’t something to hide. It’s not a flaw to fix or a ‘before’ version of yourself. It’s a body that carries you, supports you, and deserves to be seen without shame. Society might glorify one shape, but beauty has never been one-size-fits-all. So wear the outfit, take the picture, take up space. You are allowed to feel beautiful exactly as you are.
